The paper deals with video representation and captioning, which are primarily computer vision and natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also deals with language generation, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible category. The paper also proposes a new approach that reduces computation operations while attaining more non-linearity, which falls under the category of optimization and could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with video analysis, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
